Specification:

School scheduling
Students will log in to access their calendar.
They will be able to enrol in courses adding specific in-class times to their calendar.
They will add tasks with a specified number of hours they would like to spend working on it, how long a work entities.session should be, and a time/date by which they would like it to be complete.
A calendar will algorithmicallychedule

Entities:
Student
Course
Calendar (daily, weekly, monthly)
Event (assignment, reading, etc)

Use Cases:
StudentManager - manage student entityi, login status, changing names, student info
CourseManager - make new course entity, delete course entity, change a course
use_cases.usecases.CalendarManager - check if adding course is viable, add courses, to calendar, add assignments to calendar, add tasks to calendar, change display to weekly calendar, daily calendar
TaskManager - creating and changing tasks

Controller
MainConroller - run main program (HTML, or consol, communicate to other controllers to initialize, open gateway to first read from JSON file)
IO controller
Gateway: JSON

Command Line Interface:
Format: console initially, HTML/CSS implementation
